        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And the myth of the struggling artist can be a supportive crutch for the artist unwilling to pick themselves.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "The same can be said for all the people who think they're no good at math, can’t dance, or aren’t creative. Saying “I’m not built that way” is self-reassuring as much as it is self-sabotaging.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "The converse is also true.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Believing you can (despite no actual evidence) can be a powerful antidote against self-doubt.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And “acting as if” can often be a sure-fire route to building the credibility, confidence and feedback cycles you need to thrive.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "If your narrative or posture doesn’t serve you,",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "change it",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ".",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}